  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2017-06-28T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Commercial Flight Courtesy Act of 2017\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Transportation (DOT) to issue regulations prohibiting an individual on an aircraft from engaging in voice communications using a mobile device during a flight in scheduled passenger interstate or intrastate air transportation. DOT must exempt from the prohibition: (1) members of the flight crew on duty on an aircraft, and (2) federal law enforcement officers acting in an official capacity."
  }, 
